6.3 Insert links, but only those missing from current buffer
============================================================

As a variation on the ‘denote-link-add-links’ command, one may wish to
only include ’missing links’, i.e.  links that are not yet present in
the current file.

   This can be achieved with ‘denote-link-add-missing-links’.  The
command is similar to ‘denote-link-add-links’, but will only include
links to notes that are not yet linked to (*note Insert links matching a
regexp::).


